A middle-aged man had died in an auto accident at Obinaetiti Akwuzu by Nteje-Onitsha expressway, Anambra State. The crash, which occurred Friday night, involved a blue Mercedes 911 and a Honda Accord car. An eye witness said the Honda driver was trailing closely behind the truck when the driver suddenly applied brake on sighting a heap of sand ahead of him. “The Honda driver following behind on speed didn’t watch and rammed into the 911 and crashed,” he added. Confirming the incident, Sector Commander, Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Adeoye Irelewuyi attributed the cause of the crash to obsrutction and excessive speed.   Dele Adeleke: When family ties are not enough     Haruna Samuel: The Airman and the Greek gift     EFCC arraigns ex-bank director over alleged N26.6bn fraud   - Advertisement - He commiserated with the deceased family, warning motoring public against excessive speed and to be at alert while driving. Read Also: ERNEST SHONEKAN’S WIDOW: My husband died of acute pneumonia He said, “A fatal Road traffic crash occurred at Obinaetiti Akwuzu by Nteje-Onitsha Expressway, yesterday, 21st January 2022. At about 19:30hours “The crash was between two vehicles, an unidentified driver of a Blue Mercedes 911 with registration number: XA129AWK and unidentified driver of a Honda Accord car with registration number: RBX155PC. “Three male adults were involved in the crash. One male adult (the Honda driver) was killed while two male adults were rescued unhurt. “The dead victim was deposited at Wisdom Mortuary, Awkuzu. The truck was taken to FRSC base Nteje and efforts are being made by the rescue team to clear the obstruction.”